title: From secret cults to Christianity, how did ancient Roman religion change so dramatically?
description: Ancient Rome didn’t abandon its gods overnight. The rise of Christianity was a slow transformation of the cult-based religious order that had structured Roman life for centuries

title: Hypatia Taught Science in Ancient Times, and Was Killed for It
description: Hypatia of Alexandria, a renowned mathematician and philosopher, taught in the ancient world when few women had such opportunities. Her life as a public intellectual and advisor ended tragically in 415 A.D. when she was brutally murdered by Christian zealots, a stark reminder of the dangers knowledge can pose to power.
